#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "To enable policy enforcement for your application, add the following property to your *keycloak.json* file:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```json\n"
"{\n"
"  \"policy-enforcer\": {}\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
"Or a little more verbose if you want to manually define the resources being protected:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```json\n"
"{\n"
"  \"policy-enforcer\": {\n"
"    \"user-managed-access\" : {},\n"
"    \"enforcement-mode\" : \"ENFORCING\"\n"
"    \"paths\": [\n"
"      {\n"
"        \"path\" : \"/someUri/*\",\n"
"        \"methods\" : [\n"
"          {\n"
"            \"method\": \"GET\",\n"
"            \"scopes\" : [\"urn:app.com:scopes:view\"]\n"
"          },\n"
"          {\n"
"            \"method\": \"POST\",\n"
"            \"scopes\" : [\"urn:app.com:scopes:create\"]\n"
"          }\n"
"        ]\n"
"      },\n"
"      {\n"
"        \"name\" : \"Some Resource\",\n"
"        \"path\" : \"/usingPattern/{id}\",\n"
"        \"methods\" : [\n"
"          {\n"
"            \"method\": \"DELETE\",\n"
"            \"scopes\" : [\"urn:app.com:scopes:delete\"]\n"
"          }\n"
"        ]\n"
"      },\n"
"      {\n"
"        \"path\" : \"/exactMatch\"\n"
"      },\n"
"      {\n"
"        \"name\" : \"Admin Resources\",\n"
"        \"path\" : \"/usingWildCards/*\"\n"
"      }\n"
"    ]\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "Here is a description of each configuration option:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "*policy-enforcer*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Specifies the configuration options that define how policies are actually enforced and optionally the paths you want to protect. If not specified, the policy enforcer queries the server\n"
"for all resources associated with the resource server being protected. In this case, you need to ensure the resources are properly configured with a <<_resource_create_uri, URI>> property that matches the paths you want to protect.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "** *user-managed-access*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "Specifies that the adapter uses the UMA protocol. If specified, the adapter queries the server for permission tickets and return them to clients according to the UMA specification. If not specified, the adapter relies on the requesting party token (RPT) sent to the server to enforce permissions.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "** *enforcement-mode*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "Specifies how policies are enforced.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "*** *ENFORCING*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "(default mode) Requests are denied by default even when there is no policy associated with a given resource.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "*** *PERMISSIVE*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "Requests are allowed even when there is no policy associated with a given resource.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "*** *DISABLED*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "Completely disables the evaluation of policies and allows access to any resource.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "** *on-deny-redirect-to*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "Defines a URL where a client request is redirected when an \"access denied\" message is obtained from the server. By default, the adapter responds with a 403 HTTP status code.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "** *paths*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "Specifies the paths to protect.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "*** *name*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"The name of a resource on the server that is to be associated with a given path. When used in conjunction with a *path*, the policy enforcer ignores the resource's *URI* property and uses the path you provided instead.\n"
"*** *path*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"(required) A URI relative to the application's context path. If this option is specified, the policy enforcer queries the server for a resource with a *URI* with the same value.\n"
"Currently a very basic logic for path matching is supported. Examples of valid paths are:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**** Wildcards: `/*`\n"
"**** Suffix: `/*.html`\n"
"**** Sub-paths: `/path/*`\n"
"**** Path parameters: /resource/{id}\n"
"**** Exact match: /resource\n"
"**** Patterns: /{version}/resource, /api/{version}/resource, /api/{version}/resource/*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"*** *methods*\n"
"The HTTP methods (for example, GET, POST, PATCH) to protect and how they are associated with the scopes for a given resource in the server.\n"
"+[/'']\n"
"**** *method*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "The name of the HTTP method.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "**** *scopes*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "An array of strings with the scopes associated with the method. When you associate scopes with a specific method, the client trying to access a protected resource (or path) must provide an RPT that grants permission to all scopes specified in the list. For example, if you define a method _POST_ with a scope _create_, the RPT must contain a permission granting access to the _create_ scope when performing a POST to the path.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "*** *enforcement-mode*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "**** *ENFORCING*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "**** *DISABLED*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid "Disables the evaluation of policies for a path\n"
msgstr ""
